## Test: deny_both_001 — Action 2: both client ($1,957.50) and DOL ($1,957.50) adjusted income above A1E 2026 standard ($1,845) — deny

```catala
#[test]
declaration scope TestDenyBoth001:
  result scope Eligibility.EligibilityDecision

scope TestDenyBoth001:
  definition result.client_data equals Eligibility.ClientData {
    -- gross_earned_income: $4,000
    -- federal_exclusions: $0
    -- eitc_exclusion: $0
    -- irregular_earned_income: $0
    -- student_earned_income: $0
    -- student_monthly_limit: $0
    -- non_needs_based_unearned_remainder: $20
    -- impairment_work_expenses: $0
    -- blind_work_expenses: $0
    -- self_support_exclusion: $0
    -- household_type: A1E
    -- benefit_year: 2026
  }
  definition result.d_o_l_record equals Eligibility.DOLRecord {
    -- dol_earned_income_available: true
    -- dol_quarterly_earnings: $12,000
    -- gross_earned_income: $4,000
    -- federal_exclusions: $0
    -- eitc_exclusion: $0
    -- irregular_earned_income: $0
    -- student_earned_income: $0
    -- student_monthly_limit: $0
    -- non_needs_based_unearned_remainder: $20
    -- impairment_work_expenses: $0
    -- blind_work_expenses: $0
    -- self_support_exclusion: $0
  }
  assertion (result.eligible = Deny)
  assertion (result.reasons = [ IncomeExceedsStandardBoth ])
```

## Test: deny_client_001 — Action 3: client adjusted $2,457.50 above standard; DOL $457.50 below — deny on client statement regardless of DOL

```catala
#[test]
declaration scope TestDenyClient001:
  result scope Eligibility.EligibilityDecision

scope TestDenyClient001:
  definition result.client_data equals Eligibility.ClientData {
    -- gross_earned_income: $5,000
    -- federal_exclusions: $0
    -- eitc_exclusion: $0
    -- irregular_earned_income: $0
    -- student_earned_income: $0
    -- student_monthly_limit: $0
    -- non_needs_based_unearned_remainder: $20
    -- impairment_work_expenses: $0
    -- blind_work_expenses: $0
    -- self_support_exclusion: $0
    -- household_type: A1E
    -- benefit_year: 2026
  }
  definition result.d_o_l_record equals Eligibility.DOLRecord {
    -- dol_earned_income_available: true
    -- dol_quarterly_earnings: $3,000
    -- gross_earned_income: $1,000
    -- federal_exclusions: $0
    -- eitc_exclusion: $0
    -- irregular_earned_income: $0
    -- student_earned_income: $0
    -- student_monthly_limit: $0
    -- non_needs_based_unearned_remainder: $20
    -- impairment_work_expenses: $0
    -- blind_work_expenses: $0
    -- self_support_exclusion: $0
  }
  assertion (result.eligible = Deny)
  assertion (result.reasons = [ IncomeExceedsStandardClientOnly ])
```

